passages.text: As yields go down M&A goes up.

August supply is likely completed with issuance just shy of \(\) 100bn.\(July's supply was\) \ \(83bn\) total - these are the only two months this year with supply below \(\) 100bn\(. From January - June supply ranged from\) \ \(103 - 193bn\) month. There has been \(\) 9bn\(of M&A related issuance this month which is\) 9\% \(of the total. This is about in - line with the YTD share as well, which is near\) 10\% \(Based on publicly announced deals and our analysts' estimates of the funding that will come to the HG bond market from them we expect another\) \ \(36bn\) of M&A issuance from September - December. If accurate total M&A supply this year would be in - line with our 2025 M&A issuance forecast of \(\sim\) 150bn. However, M&A headlines have surged with 3 big deals announced recently, to be funded in 2026 - Keurig Dr. Pepper / Peet's, AT&T / EchoStar and Amphenol / CommScope. The 2026 pipeline for M&A issuance is already at \(\) 73bn\(with January still four months away. So 2026 is setting up to be a large year for M&A related supply. This is consistent with our expectation for the Fed to lower rates by\) 100bp between now and the January FOMC meeting. M&A is broadly driven by two factors: low funding costs and bullish economic growth expectations. Both of these are in the direction of JPM's forecasts for 2026.

- The JULI spread widened by 1bp on Wednesday to 88bp, while the yield fell by 1bp to \(5.29\%\) (Table 1).

- There was no High Grade Issuance on Wednesday. WTD \(\) 3bn\(has been issued. MTD\) \ \(99bn\) has been issued. YTD supply totals \(\) 1092bn\(. Issuance in August has averaged\) \ \(9bn\) over the past four years.
- Bonds issued over the past 10 days are up wider than at issuance on average (based on \(\) 20bn\(across 29 JULI eligible bonds), while the index overall is 3bp wider over the same time period.

- Trading activity in HG bonds was \(\) 33.2bn\(on Wednesday (2w average\) \ \(29.9bn / day\) , YTD average \(\) 38.5bn/day). Dealers were net buyers of \(\) 794\mathrm{mn}\(of bonds (1w avg\) \ \(448\mathrm{mn / day}\) buying, 3m avg \(\) 342\mathrm{mn / day}\) selling). Dealers net bought \(\) 2.2bn\(of bonds from investors over the past 5 days and net bought\) \ \(2.7bn\) of bonds from investors over the past 10 days. \(10.6\%\) of trading yesterday was executed through Portfolio Trades and over the past 5 days this figure is \(13.5\%\) . Over the 5 day period \(\) 2.9bn\(of new HG bonds were issued.

- Our estimate of dealer net positions in corporate bonds \(>13\mathrm{m}\) increased by \(\) 793\mathrm{mn}\(on Wednesday (this includes TRACE and ETF data). On the week this estimate of positions is up by\) \ \(753\mathrm{mn}\) to \(-\) 4.1bn, which is at the \(27\%\) level in the 3m range. Within the last 3m range, positions are at the \(11\%\) level in the 1-5yr bucket, at the \(98\%\) level in the 5-10yr bucket, and at the \(22\%\) level in the \(10+\) yr bucket (Table 5).

- The \(3s5s\) curve is trading at \(14\mathrm{bp}\) (40% of its 1m range), \(5s10s\) is trading at \(25\mathrm{bp}\) (100% of its 1m range) and \(10s30s\) is trading at \(10\mathrm{bp}\) (0% of its 1m range). Please see our Curveball: HG Credit Curve Opportunities for details on the bond pairs which comprise these curves and the steepest/flattest ones in each segment (Table 3).

- Our new Credit Relative Value Screen highlights several relationships which are out of line with their historical trading patterns: B3 US Leveraged Loans are tight to B2 US Leveraged Loans, CCC US Leveraged Loans are wide to B3 US Leveraged Loans, CDX.IG is tight to iTraxx Main, 10y A-rated bonds are wide to 10y AA Taxable Munis and 5y US HG bonds are wide to MBS Current Coupon.
- HG bonds are trading 54bp wide to their respective CDS, on average. In relative terms, this is the widest that HG bonds have traded to their CDS since mid July 2025 (Table 4).
- HY bonds are trading 99bp wide to their respective CDS, on average. In relative terms, this is the widest that HY bonds have traded to their CDS since early July 2025 (Table 4).
- JULI 7-10yr Dispersion/Spread Ratio is currently at \(15\%\) , at its lowest level since early April 2025 (Table 4).

- CDX.IG 5y index widened by 0.5bp on Wednesday to 50.3bp. CDX.IG underperformed its underlying CDS by 1bp on Wednesday and is trading 1bp rich to its fair value (Table 7). Please see today's CDX.IG Analytics for more details.

- The 25 largest HG Credit ETFs had combined inflows of \(\) 133\mathrm{mn}\(on Wednesday (0.05% of AUM). This compares to\)\\(1.4bn\) of inflows (0.51% of AUM) over the week and \(\) 10.6bn\(of inflows (3.99% of AUM) over the month.

- CDX.HY 5y index sold-off by 15c/3bp on Wednesday to \(\) 107.3/315bp\(. CDX.HY underperformed its underlying CDS by 24c/6bp on Wednesday and is trading 30c/7bp rich to its fair value (Table 7). Please see today's CDX.HY Analytics for more details.

- The 25 largest HY Credit ETFs had combined outflows of \(\) 213\mathrm{mn}\(on Wednesday (- 0.21\% of AUM). This compares to\)\\(421\mathrm{mn}\) outflows (- 0.42% of AUM) over the week and \(\) 812\mathrm{mn}\(inflows (0.82\% of AUM) over the month.
